                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.093,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The second case is also technical, but ordinarily a federal litigant who is too poor -- it\u0027s called Coleman v. Tollefson."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.093,
                                "stop": 20.62,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Ordinarily, a federal litigant who is too poor to pay court fees can proceed in forma pauperis."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.62,
                                "stop": 30.76,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That means he doesn\u0027t have to pay all the fees, but a special statutory provision sets forth what we colloquially call the three strikes rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.76,
                                "stop": 64.533,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It says that a court cannot grant a federal prisoner an in forma pauperis status in a civil case where that litigant, that prisoner, \u201chas, on three or more prior occasions, while incarcerated brought an action or appeal in a court of the United States which action or appeal was dismissed on the grounds that it is frivolous, malicious, or fails to state a claim upon which relief may be granted.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.533,
                                "stop": 67.898,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So three times that happens, and you are out."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.898,
                                "stop": 85.655,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In this case, a prisoner Andrew Lee Coleman wants to bring a federal civil case and he wants to proceed in forma pauperis even though courts have dismissed three of his earlier cases on the grounds that the statute lists."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.655,
                                "stop": 99.028,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "He says, \u201cI can bring the case nonetheless in forma pauperis, because at the time I first filed this -- call it a fourth case -- one of those earlier three dismissals was still on appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.028,
                                "stop": 113.649,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For that reason, because the appeals court had not yet decided whether the district court\u0027s dismissal in the third one was correct or incorrect, that dismissal, he says, \u201cshould not count as my third strike.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.649,
                                "stop": 118.894,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In his view, \u201cwhen I brought the case, I hadn\u0027t struck out yet.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.894,
                                "stop": 120.991,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We do not agree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.991,
                                "stop": 141.803,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The literal language of the statute says that the courts are to account as a strike \u201can action or appeal that was dismissed on certain occasions, prior occasions, and each of the petitioner\u0027s three prior actions was dismissed on the grounds that the statute lists.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.803,
                                "stop": 153.186,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The statute\u0027s language says nothing about any of these dismissals being provisional or being countable only when the litigant has no chance of securing a reversal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.186,
                                "stop": 161.043,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Moreover, the law ordinarily treats a trial court dismissal in the way the statute\u0027s literal language suggests."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.043,
                                "stop": 173.034,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Unless a court issues a stay, a trial court\u0027s judgment, for example dismissing a case, normally takes effect whether an appeal is pending or whether it is not pending."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.034,
                                "stop": 193.489,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A trial court\u0027s dismissal\u0027s preclusive effect normally takes place immediately whether a pending appeal exist or doesn\u0027t exist, and we normally use different words to describe two different situations a trial court\u0027s action dismissing a case - that we call a dismissal - and appellate court\u0027s action in respect to that dismissal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.489,
                                "stop": 199.895,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We normally say, the appellate court say, affirms the trial court\u0027s dismissal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.895,
                                "stop": 214.409,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Further to refuse to count of trial court\u0027s dismissal as a strike until the conclusion of an appeal would undermine the statute\u0027s basic objective, filtering out what the prisoner\u0027s history suggests may well be meritless claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.409,
                                "stop": 216.205,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Appeals take time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 216.205,
                                "stop": 224.388,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "During that time, a litigious prisoner could file more actions, perhaps many more, while everybody is waiting for the appellate court to decide."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.388,
                                "stop": 234.185,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Indeed the petitioner here filed at least four more in forma pauperis civil cases just during the time that third strike was on appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 234.185,
                                "stop": 237.379,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Finally, we recognize an argument the other way."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.379,
                                "stop": 241.087,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Coleman points out a danger in our interpretation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.087,
                                "stop": 243.813,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "He says, this is potentially unfair."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.813,
                                "stop": 252.664,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "What\u0027s supposed to happen if my third strike was appealed and the appellate court reversed it? Then I wouldn\u0027t have had three strikes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 252.664,
                                "stop": 259.958,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But we do not agree with him that this third -- this risk provides a sufficient reason for a different result."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.958,
                                "stop": 295.696,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Solicitor General points out that instances in which an appeals court reverses a third strike dismissal like this are exceedingly rare, and in any event, he, the Solicitor General, also suggests a procedural route that involves Rule 60(b) through which were that to happen, the appeals court says, you were wrong trial court and dismissing it as frivolous, there is a route, Rule 60(b), through which a litigant in such an instance could return to court, refile his dismissed action, and recover in forma pauperis status."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 295.696,
                                "stop": 297.573,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That\u0027s possibly a way out."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 297.573,
                                "stop": 307.525,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For these reasons and for others described in our opinion, we conclude that a trial court\u0027s dismissal counts as a third strike even while the case is pending on appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 307.525,
                                "stop": 313.232,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Thus, Coleman cannot proceed with his fourth and subsequent civil lawsuits in forma pauperis."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 313.232,
                                "stop": 317.556,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We affirm the similar determination of the Federal Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 317.556,
                                "stop": 321.288,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
